CHANGES0001 - Initial setup of work.agda

Summary:
- Created initial structure for formalizing "A Foundation for Synthetic Stone Duality"
- Set up basic imports from Cubical Agda library
- Defined binary sequences (binarySequence = ℕ → Bool)
- Defined Cantor space as binarySequence
- Defined biconditional (↔) for logical equivalence

Open and Closed Propositions:
- Defined isOpenProp: A proposition P is open if ∃ α : 2^ℕ such that P ↔ ∃n, α n = true
- Defined isClosedProp: A proposition P is closed if ∃ α : 2^ℕ such that P ↔ ∀n, α n = false
- Defined Open and Closed as Σ-types bundling hProps with their openness/closedness witnesses
- Proved negOpenIsClosed: negation of an open proposition is closed
- Proved decIsOpen: every decidable proposition is open
- Proved decIsClosed: every decidable proposition is closed

Types defined (not proved):
- MarkovPrinciple: ∀ α, ¬(∀n, α n = false) → Σn, α n = true
- WLPO: ∀ α, Dec(∀n, α n = false)
- ℕ∞: sequences hitting true at most once
- LLPO: for all α : ℕ∞, even/odd splitting property

